books.author: Jules Verne

descriptions.text: Angels and Demons, the first installment of Dan Brown's mystery thriller saga, follows symbologist Robert Langdon on an adventure to solve a historical puzzle laid across Rome.

Phileas Fogg, a London gentleman of meticulous and unchanging habits, hires as his valet Jean Passepartout, a Frenchman who has had a variety of jobs, including circus performer, but now seeks a tranquil life.

The Lost Symbol is a bestselling novel by Dan Brown and is the third to feature Harvard professor and symbology expert Robert Langdon. In this novel, Langdon makes a last-minute trip to Washington, DC, to give a keynote speech at an event hosted by his friend and mentor, Peter Solomon.

The book 'Winnie the Pooh' by A. A. Milne is a collection of short stories featuring the teddy bear of Christopher Robin named Winnie the Pooh. These stories are a narrative within a narrative, where the narrator narrates these stories about Winnie the Pooh to Christopher Robin.
